\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The Big Picture \
We set up an Automated Testing Suite. Before this, you had to manually run the app, upload a PDF, and click buttons to see if anything broke. Now, Python does this automatically in seconds to verify your logic is sound. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 We created three main test files and one automation file. Here is what each one does: \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 1. 
\f3\b tests/test_parser.py
\f2\b0  (Testing the Data Logic) \
What it does: Tests the code that processes the raw text returned by AI.\
Why it matters: AI often returns messy data (e.g., inside markdown code blocks 
\f3\b ```json ...
\f2\b0  ). This file ensures your code is robust enough to clean that up. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_clean_json...
\f2\b0 : Verifies that the code removes markdown backticks and fixes syntax errors (like trailing commas) so Python can read the JSON.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_regex_fallback...
\f2\b0 : If the AI fails completely, your code uses "Regex" (pattern matching) to find data like 
\f3\b Title: ...
\f2\b0  or 
\f3\b Year: ...
\f2\b0 . These tests check if that backup plan works.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_parse_result_success
\f2\b0 : Uses Mocking to simulate a perfect AI response. It ensures your code correctly converts that response into the final result format.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 2. 
\f3\b tests/test_utils.py
\f2\b0  (Testing the Tools) \
What it does: Tests helper functions, specifically PDF reading and text resizing.\
Why it matters: Reading PDFs is slow and unpredictable. We tested it without actually opening a PDF file. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_preprocess_text...
\f2\b0 : Checks if long text is correctly shortened to save money on API tokens.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_extract_pdf_content
\f2\b0 : This used Mocking heavily. We pretended to be PyMuPDF (the PDF library). We told the test: 
\f4\i "If the app asks for a PDF, don't open a real one\'97just give it this fake text instead."
\f2\i0  This proves your PDF reading logic works without needing a physical file.\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 3. 
\f3\b tests/test_app.py
\f2\b0  (Testing the User Interface) \
What it does: Tests the Streamlit app flow itself.\
Why it matters: Ensures the app doesn't crash when a user interacts with it. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_app_initial_render
\f2\b0 : Loads the app in a "headless" browser (no UI). It simulates a user who has already accepted the disclaimer and checks if the main menu appears.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 
\f3\b test_screener_mode_selection
\f2\b0 : Simulates a user clicking the "Select Screener" button. It checks if the app correctly switches the mode from the menu to the screener.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 4. 
\f3\b .github/workflows/python-app.yml
\f2\b0  \
What it does: This is the CI/CD Pipeline.\
Why it matters: It automates the tests so you don't have to run them. \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 The Process: Every time you push code to GitHub, this file wakes up a virtual server on GitHub. It installs Python, installs your requirements, and runs 
\f3\b pytest
\f2\b0 .\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 The Result: If you break something (e.g., a syntax error), GitHub will send you a red "X" and tell you which test failed. If it passes, you get a green checkmark.\
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Key Concept: "Mocking" \
You probably noticed we used 
\f3\b @patch
\f2\b0  and 
\f3\b MagicMock
\f2\b0  a lot. \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 Real World: Calling OpenAI costs money and takes time. Reading a PDF requires a file on your disk.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 Testing World: We don't want to spend money or need files. We Mock these dependencies.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 Translation: "Hey Python, when the code tries to call 
\f3\b openai.chat
\f2\b0 , don't actually call it. Just pretend it happened and return this fake string I wrote down."\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
